snippet.textDisplay: She knocked it out in Consumer Affairs, and I was really hoping she would run.  Then she was Senator and I was excited she had an opportunity to contribute to the Legislative Branch.  I was a big fan of her presidential run, but she seemed to be trying to out Bernie Bernie and I am just not down for such big swings too far the other way too fast.  Obama was center-left and so was Clinton.  I wish Warren was down for moderation and a slower march to progress because I think we are still shellshocked by the idiot who out gamed the Electoral College a few years ago.  Let's heal for a bit, and push for some more progressive agenda items in our second term!  Obamacare would have worked had it not been neutered and packed with riders and compromises to buy off swing voters in Congress.  Warren for FTC or the Cabinet definitely.  Vice president?  Sure.  I just wish she had tempered things for the election and won.  Now we get Biden, who is the lesser of two evils vs. Trump, or Bernie which I will vote for if forced, just because I cannot stand another Trump term.
snippet.textOriginal: She knocked it out in Consumer Affairs, and I was really hoping she would run.  Then she was Senator and I was excited she had an opportunity to contribute to the Legislative Branch.  I was a big fan of her presidential run, but she seemed to be trying to out Bernie Bernie and I am just not down for such big swings too far the other way too fast.  Obama was center-left and so was Clinton.  I wish Warren was down for moderation and a slower march to progress because I think we are still shellshocked by the idiot who out gamed the Electoral College a few years ago.  Let's heal for a bit, and push for some more progressive agenda items in our second term!  Obamacare would have worked had it not been neutered and packed with riders and compromises to buy off swing voters in Congress.  Warren for FTC or the Cabinet definitely.  Vice president?  Sure.  I just wish she had tempered things for the election and won.  Now we get Biden, who is the lesser of two evils vs. Trump, or Bernie which I will vote for if forced, just because I cannot stand another Trump term.
